.SH "NAME"
IO::Interactive::Tiny \- is_interactive() without large deps
.SH "VERSION"
.IX Header "VERSION"
This document describes IO::Interactive::Tiny version 0.2
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use IO::Interactive::Tiny;
\&
\&    if ( IO::Interactive::Tiny::is_interactive() ) {
\&        print "I probably want text output.";
\&    }
\&    else {
\&        print "I probably want HTML output."; 
\&    }
.Ve
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Provides the useful subset of IO::InteractiveXs functionality in the form of only having \fIis_interactive()\fR.
.PP
Also gains ::Tiny\-ness by not using version, Carp, or Scalar::Util
.SH "INTERFACE"
.IX Header "INTERFACE"
Nothing in exported or exportable, that helps keep it '::Tiny'.
.SS "\fIIO::Interactive::Tiny::is_interactive()\fP"
.IX Subsection "IO::Interactive::Tiny::is_interactive()"
Same functionality as \*(L"\fIis_interactive()\fR\*(R" in IO::Interactive:.
.SH "DIAGNOSTICS"
.IX Header "DIAGNOSTICS"
IO::Interactive::Tiny throws no warnings or errors of its own.
.SH "CONFIGURATION AND ENVIRONMENT"
.IX Header "CONFIGURATION AND ENVIRONMENT"
IO::Interactive::Tiny requires no configuration files or environment variables.
.SH "DEPENDENCIES"
.IX Header "DEPENDENCIES"
None.
.SH "INCOMPATIBILITIES"
.IX Header "INCOMPATIBILITIES"
None reported.
.SH "BUGS AND LIMITATIONS"
.IX Header "BUGS AND LIMITATIONS"
No bugs have been reported.
.PP
Please report any bugs or feature requests to
\&\f(CW\*(C`bug\-io\-interactive\-tiny@rt.cpan.org\*(C'\fR, or through the web interface at
<http://rt.cpan.org>.
